Two AP officers were hospitalised after they shot each other in an argument while manning a KCPE exams container in Sotik on Thursday night. The two turned on each other at the Sotik subcounty commissioner's office after a brief exchange at about 8.30pm.They were rushed to Tenwek Mission Hospital where they are admitted in critical condition.Commanders from Bomet and Sotik found two G3 rifles at the scene when they visited. They launched an investigation.Read: Cop kills OCS, seven officers in 8-hour Kapenguria shooting